result.adr_address: 8 Holland St, Kennedy Town, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 8 Holland St, Kennedy Town, Hong Kong
result.name: Alvy's

reviews.text: Pick something you like at do it well. That seems to be Alvy’s adage to serving up options for food and drinks in Kennedy Town.  Worth a detour if it’s not in your neighborhood.  An easy spot to enjoy some diner and drinks with friends.

Very nice sourdough pizzas served here. Quaint little restaurant and they do have a decent selection of craft beers to go with your pizzas. Wine list also includes organic wines so that's definitely a plus. Wish the service staff would be a little more enthusiastic though. Otherwise a great place to hang out with friends.
Their classic G&T with Ford's gin was very smooth. Paired it with the Alvy's classic and it was a great way to cap off the night. Definitely some of the best pizza in Hong Kong.

Nice place for food with a twist. Can see that they are making an effort to be creative and I think it's a success. Will go there again. Good selection of local craft beer. Good vibe. Not for a quiet conversation.

Love their hit wings even though it's a bit spicy for me.

Pepperoni pizza is terrific. But the service needs a lot of work. Least customer centric bunch of dopes going particularly the female waitress. When I asked for pepper she actually rolled her eyes at her colleague because she was annoyed he hadn’t dealt with me (he was busy working at the bar)

The chilli flake jar needs changing as the holes are too small for them to escape and the pepper grinder doesn’t work. You should probably have slight flexibility on a small change such as red sauce instead of white sauce - will it kill you?
